  "description": [
    "CIO Demands PostWar Jobs Aid to Helpless PHILADELPHIA Nov 6 Essentials for a sound postwar program were laid down In a resolution passed by unanimous vote of the CIO Convention in session here this week These essentials are B 1 A Job at union wages or a farm business or profession that pays X A wellbuilt convenient home decently furnished 8 Good food clothing and med ical care 4 Good schooling for children with an equal chance for a healthy and happy growth 5 An income through social In surance In case of sickness old age early death of the wage earner ox unemployment 8 Guarantee of tlio right of every worker to Join a union of his own choosing and to enjoy the benefits of collective bargaining Victory in the peace Involves the accompaniment of these ends and It Is the task and responsibility of labor to see that It does not be come merely a pious slogan the resolution declared BROAD OUTLINE Speaking In support of the reso lution John Brophy director of Industrial Union Councils and member of the ClOs PostWar Planning Committee said that the NFU Head Soys Farmers Labor Must Work Together To Help Win"
  ],
